Finally, if we take the Sum of all salaries, we can estimate a budget for each college. I do the simple SQL Query below:

SELECT SUM(DISTINCT `Base Pay`), College, Year
FROM salaries_final
GROUP BY College, Year

The corresponding chart comparing the two Colleges is below:

In the chart, you can see that in 2009, money allocated to CAS was higher, but by 2020 COM overtakes it. Furthermore, according to an article, CAS
already has a shortfall of 27 million for the year 2020.
